#### 4.7.13 Request Body Object

[](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.1.html#request-body-object)

Describes a single request body.

##### 4.7.13.1 Fixed Fields

[](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.1.html#fixed-fields-10)

| Field Name | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| description | `string` | A brief description of the request body. This could contain examples of use. \[[CommonMark](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.1.html#bib-commonmark "CommonMark Spec")\] syntax *MAY* be used for rich text representation. |
| content | Map\[`string`, [Media Type Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.1.html#media-type-object)\] | ***REQUIRED***. The content of the request body. The key is a media type or media type range, see \[[RFC7231](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.1.html#bib-rfc7231 "Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP/1.1): Semantics and Content")\] [Appendix D](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#appendix-D), and the value describes it. For requests that match multiple keys, only the most specific key is applicable. e.g. text/plain overrides text/\* |
| required | `boolean` | Determines if the request body is required in the request. Defaults to `false`. |

This object *MAY* be extended with [Specification Extensions](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.1.html#specification-extensions).

##### 4.7.13.2 Request Body Examples

[](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.1.html#request-body-examples)

A request body with a referenced model definition.

```
{
  "description": "user to add to the system",
  "content": {
    "application/json": {
      "schema": {
        "$ref": "#/components/schemas/User"
      },
      "examples": {
