#### 4.7.9 Path Item Object

[](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#path-item-object)

Describes the operations available on a single path. A Path Item *MAY* be empty, due to [ACL constraints](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#security-filtering). The path itself is still exposed to the documentation viewer but they will not know which operations and parameters are available.

##### 4.7.9.1 Fixed Fields

[](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#fixed-fields-6)

| Field Name | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| $ref | `string` | Allows for an external definition of this path item. The referenced structure *MUST* be in the format of a [Path Item Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#path-item-object). If there are conflicts between the referenced definition and this Path Item’s definition, the behavior is *undefined*. |
| summary | `string` | An optional, string summary, intended to apply to all operations in this path. |
| description | `string` | An optional, string description, intended to apply to all operations in this path. \[[CommonMark](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#bib-commonmark "CommonMark Spec")\] syntax *MAY* be used for rich text representation. |
| get | [Operation Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#operation-object) | A definition of a GET operation on this path. |
| put | [Operation Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#operation-object) | A definition of a PUT operation on this path. |
| post | [Operation Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#operation-object) | A definition of a POST operation on this path. |
| delete | [Operation Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#operation-object) | A definition of a DELETE operation on this path. |
| options | [Operation Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#operation-object) | A definition of a OPTIONS operation on this path. |
| head | [Operation Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#operation-object) | A definition of a HEAD operation on this path. |
| patch | [Operation Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#operation-object) | A definition of a PATCH operation on this path. |
| trace | [Operation Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#operation-object) | A definition of a TRACE operation on this path. |
| servers | \[[Server Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#server-object)\] | An alternative `server` array to service all operations in this path. |
| parameters | \[[Parameter Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#parameter-object) | [Reference Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#reference-object)\] | A list of parameters that are applicable for all the operations described under this path. These parameters can be overridden at the operation level, but cannot be removed there. The list *MUST NOT* include duplicated parameters. A unique parameter is defined by a combination of a [name](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#parameterName) and [location](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#parameterIn). The list can use the [Reference Object](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#reference-object) to link to parameters that are defined at the [OpenAPI Object’s components/parameters](https:

//spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#componentsParameters). |

This object *MAY* be extended with [Specification Extensions](https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.2.html#specification-extensions).

